# Morph across slides

Give an element on this slide and one on the next the **same `data-morph`** key
and it animates from where it was — a magic-move *across the slide transition*.

**No setup at all** — the addon wires this globally, so it just works:

```mdc
---
transition: slide-left
morph: { duration: 0.4 }   # the leaving slide owns the effect
---
<div data-morph="hero">A</div>
```

Tune it from **frontmatter** — deck headmatter `morph:` for defaults, the
**leaving** slide's `morph:` for that transition. Runs **during** any transition
(here: `slide-left`). Press <kbd>→</kbd>.

