# `usePos` — reactive anchors

`pos("selector@anchor")` resolves a live point on a DOM element — re-measured
every frame, so it tracks layout, GSAP moves and resizes.

```ts
const pos = usePos()

// anchors: c · t · b · l · r · tl · tr · bl · br
pos(".card@tr")     // top-right corner
pos(".card@center") // (center is the default)

// reactive vector math
pos(".card@r")[0].add(20, 0) // right edge + 20
pos(".card@tl")[0].H(other)  // x of other, y of .card

// fan-out — one entry per matching element
pos(".item@center")            // [p0, p1, p2, …]
```

