# `useTwo` — reactive arrows

`mkArrow(from, to, props)` draws a Two.js arrow whose endpoints are resolved
**every frame**. Pass anchor strings directly — no `pos()` wrapper needed.

```ts
const arrow = two.back.mkArrow(".a@r", ".b@l", {
  linewidth: 3, stroke: "#0ea5e9",
})

tl.step()
  .from(arrow, { end: 0 }) // draw it
  .step()
  .to(".b", { x: 100 }) // move the target…
  .step()               // …arrow follows live
```

