# `useTwo` — SVG-style paths

`mkPath` is config-first; the first point is a `.M()` command, then chain
SVG-like commands. Upper-case = absolute, lower-case = relative.

```ts
two.back.mkPath({
    stroke: "#6366f1",
    head: "triangle",
    radius: 14,
    text: "route",   // label at the midpoint
  })
  .M(".p-from@r") // moveto (start)
  .h(28)          // relative h-line
  .V(".p-to@l")   // absolute v-line
  .H(".p-to@l")   // absolute h-line (try VH instead)
  // (.L .Z … also exist)
  // also try the VH, HV, VHV, and HVH
```

`radius` rounds the corners, `head` adds an arrowhead, and `from(path,{end:0})`
animates it.

