# `useTwo` — circles & layers

`mkCircle(center, radius, props)`. Every `useTwo` exposes two layers:
`two.back` renders **behind** the slide's HTML, `two.front` **on top** of it.

```ts
two.back.mkCircle(".stack@tr",
  50, { fill: "#60a5fa66" })  // behind
two.front.mkCircle(".stack@br",
  25, { fill: "#34d39988" }) // on top
```

The blue ring is occluded by the card (it's on the back layer); the green disk
covers it (front layer).

